<font color="#FF0000">SMALL WEEDS</font><br>
<tt>Sun Apr 27 22:59:27 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
&quot;doc&quot; Barry,<br><br>
I know that you are not the &quot;hate crime&quot; type racist.  I appreciate what Betty put on her posting, and do wish to clarify.  What I want you, especially, to understand (because you are thinking things through, and modifying your behavior) is that there is an incidious, persistant racism within our culture.  This racism is a remnant of over 200 years of official racism, and can be as seemingly innocuous as that one golfer's comment about Tigar Woods.  <br><br>
But even so, they hurt, often in ways not initially understood.  I lost an 18 year job, in part because I could never become close to a branch manager who persisted in using racial jokes (for instance, asking about the &quot;slanty-eyed peas in my oriental salad during a business lunch).  I called him on it, privately in a letter.  After that, I was never with the &quot;in&quot; group, and when it came time to down-size, I was the one they manufactured stuff about in order to justify firing me.<br><br>
So you see, when we see seemingly inocent remarks, or aimed small barbs, Doc Del and I tend to object.  We have seen this kind of thinking esculate into the actual taking of lives.  <br><br>
It is like a weed which needs to be pulled from a garden before it takes over.  People might object to our pulling of the small weeds, but when they become large, with their roots established, me might have to pull out the shrubs we want to get to the weeds.<br><br>
Think it over, then go over to Little Saigon and learn a bit more obout these people.  You may be surprised.
<p><code>-- searat@sorcom.com  (John C. Ratliff) </code><p>


